description.narrative:
1. Enhanced partnership between the central and provincial DoE offices for better conservation planning and implementation;
2. Game guard training and performance monitoring to address threats to cheetah and prey;
3. Establishment of cheetah population range across the 10 habitats;
4. Formulation and execution of of new research through partnerships with international project partners;
5. Collection of field data based on agreed monitoring protocols.

a) LU drought monitoring system is established;
b) Intersectoral coordination mecchanism for drought managment created;
c) Drought risk incorporated into project work plans;
d) National and local authorities sentitized and trained.
